§4 nec nunc infecunditate laboratur, ‘its troubles are not even now due to any lack of fertility'. The decay of farming in Italy, ascribed by Varro to the preference by the peasantry of an idle life in Rome, by Pliny to the prevalence of ‘latifundia' and slave labour, was perhaps principally due on the economic side to the fact that grain imported frorn Africa and Sicily cost less than that raised in Italy.
